  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I told him I liked him and he didn't give me an actual answer! Help?",
  "response": "It can be really frustrating and confusing when you express your feelings to someone and don't get a clear response. Here\u2019s how you might want to handle the situation:\n\n1. **Give Him Some Time**: Sometimes, people need a little time to process their feelings and think about how they want to respond. He might be feeling surprised or unsure about how he feels and just needs some time to figure it out.\n\n2. **Communicate Again**: If a few days have passed and he hasn\u2019t brought it up, it might be worth having another conversation. You can say something like, \"I wanted to talk about what I said the other day. I felt a bit unsure because I didn't get a clear response from you. Can we talk about it?\"\n\n3. **Be Direct but Kind**: When you talk to him again, try to be clear about what you need. You might say, \"I really value our friendship, but I also have feelings for you. It\u2019s important for me to know how you feel so I can understand where we stand.\"\n\n4. **Prepare for Any Response**: Remember, he might not feel the same way, and that\u2019s okay. It\u2019s important to be prepared for any response and to handle it gracefully. If he doesn\u2019t feel the same way, it might hurt, but it\u2019s better to know so you can move on.\n\n5. **Take Care of Yourself**: Regardless of his response, make sure you\u2019re taking care of your emotional health. Surround yourself with friends and activities you enjoy, and give yourself time to process your feelings.\n\n6. **Consider Your Friendship**: If you want to maintain a friendship with him, you might need to take some time apart to let your feelings settle. It\u2019s okay to set boundaries that help you feel comfortable.\n\nRemember, it\u2019s brave to express your feelings, and you deserve a clear and respectful response. Whatever happens, you\u2019ve taken a step towards understanding your emotions better, and that\u2019s something to be proud of.",
